-- Coal Investor Tinkler Tops BRW Young Rich List With $590 Million Fortune
-- B y   D a n i e l   P e t r i e
-- 2010-09-29T05:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/coal-investor-tinkler-tops-brw-young-rich-list-with-590-million-fortune.html
Coal-mining investor  Nathan Tinkler 
is Australia’s wealthiest individual under the age of 40,
according to Business Review Weekly, which estimates his fortune
at A$610 million ($590 million).  Tinkler controls Aston Resources Pty Ltd., an Australian
coal developer that raised A$400 million last month through an
initial public offering.  Greg Coffey  and  Hilton Nathanson , London-based hedge fund
managers, occupy second and third positions, with wealth of
$A406 million and $A395 million, respectively. Coffey is co-
chief investment officer at Moore Capital Management LLC,  Louis M. Bacon ’s $15 billion hedge-fund firm. Nathanson set up Marble
Bar Asset Management LLP in 2002.  Sydney property developer Shaun Bonett is in fourth
position with $A360 million. Software developers and owners of
 Atlassian ,  Mike Cannon-Brookes  and  Scott Farquhar , are fifth on
the list with a combined wealth estimated at $A314 million.  There are seven women on the list, led by Nicole Patterson,
owner of insurance building and repair company, Patterson
Insurerbuild, with A$61 million. Patterson owns the company with
her husband, Stuart Patterson.  Below is a table of the top five wealthiest Australians younger
than 40:   ==============================================================  Wealth
 Rank    Name               Age   Industry         2010($AUD M)
 ==============================================================  1     Nathan Tinkler      34   Mining                  A$610  2     Greg Coffey         39   Funds Management        A$406  3     Hilton Nathanson    40   Funds Management        A$395  4     Shaun Bonett        39   Property                A$360  5*    Mike Cannon-Brookes 30   Information Technology  A$314  and Scott Farquhar  30
===============================================================
*Combined wealth. Source: Business Review Weekly  To contact the reporter on this story:
